text: Strum is a village in Trempealeau County of the state of Wisconsin in the United States. It can be found along the Buffalo River. 1,076 people were living in Strum as of the 2020 census. Strum has an area of 1.3 square miles, says the United States Census Bureau. ==References== ==Other websites== *Village of Strum *School District of Eleva-Strum Category:Trempealeau County, Wisconsin Category:Villages in Wisconsin
